# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Line endings — keep shell scripts LF even on Windows checkouts.
#
# This repo's `_py.sh` wrapper (and any other *.sh) MUST stay LF: with
# core.autocrlf=true a Windows clone would otherwise get CRLF, and bash
# then fails with `bad interpreter: /usr/bin/env bash^M`. eol=lf overrides
# autocrlf so these files are always checked out with LF. (Only shell
# scripts need this — Python/.gitignore tolerate CRLF, so they are left
# alone to avoid a noisy whole-repo renormalization.)
*.sh text eol=lf
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Internal-only trees — excluded from `git archive` exports.
#
# NOTE: the public (byungjunjang/slide-svg) mirror is a MANUAL diff-only process
# (see docs/superpowers handoff). `export-ignore` only affects archive-based
# exports — it does NOT block `git push`. This file documents intent and protects
# archive consumers; the push-based mirror still excludes these trees by hand.
docs/superpowers/ export-ignore
tests/ export-ignore
